      • createCalendarEvent

        public CalendarEvent createCalendarEvent(String channelId,
                                         String name,
                                         String description,
                                         String location,
                                         String startsAt,
                                         String url,
                                         Integer color,
                                         Integer duration,
                                         Boolean isPrivate,
                                         Integer rsvpLimit)
        Create a new calendar event.
        https://www.guilded.gg/docs/api/calendarEvents/CalendarEventCreate
        Parameters:
        channelId - The ID of the channel that the calendar event will be created in.
        name - The name of the event (min length 1, max length 60).
        description - The description of the event (min length 1, max length 8000, null if no description).
        location - The location of the event (min length 1, max length 8000, null if no location).
        startsAt - The ISO 8601 timestamp that the event starts at.
        url - A URL to associate with the event (optional).
        color - The color of the event when viewing in the calendar (from 0x000000 or 0, to 0xffffff or 16777215).
        duration - The duration of the event in minutes (min 1).
        isPrivate - No description available in the API documentation.
        rsvpLimit - The number of RSVPs to allow before waitlisting RSVPs (min 1, null if you don't want to limit).
        Returns:
        The created calendar event.
